We plug in $ x = 4 $: \begin{align*}
3(4) + 2y &= 12\\
12 + 2y &= 12\\
y &= 0.
\end{align*}

Therefore, $ b = \boxed{0} $.

Substituting $ y $, we obtain $ 2x+3(34) = 4 $. Solving for $ x $, we obtain:

\begin{align*}
2x+3(34) &= 4\\
\Rightarrow \qquad 2x + 102 &= 4\\
\Rightarrow \qquad 2x &= -98\\
\Rightarrow \qquad x &= \boxed{-49}
