\end{array}
\right.\]Find $ f(f(f(f(f(f(2)))))) $.

fields.solution:
We just plug into our function definitions given in the problem:

\begin{align*}
f(g(7)) + g(f(3)) &= f(7 + 7) + g(3^2 - 1) \\
&= f(14) + g(8) = (14^2 - 1) + (8 + 7) \\
&= 195 + 15 = \boxed{210}
\end{align*}

Since we know that $ f(x)=x^3+2x+1 $ and $ g(x)=x-1 $, we can express $ f(g(1)) $ as $ (x-1)^3+2(x-1)+1 $. Thus, when $ x=1 $ we find \begin{align*} (f(g(1))&=(1-1)^3+2(1-1)+1
\\ &=(0)^3+2(0)+1
\\ &=0+0+1
\\&=\boxed{1}
\end{align*}

