Using the distributive property, we have \begin{align*}
&(2x^5 + 3x^2)(x^4 - 4x^2 + 3x - 8) \\
&\qquad= 2x^5(x^4 - 4x^2 + 3x - 8) + 3x^2(x^4 - 4x^2 + 3x - 8) \\
&\qquad= 2x^9 - 8x^7 + 6x^6 - 16x^5 + 3x^6 - 12x^4 + 9x^3 - 24x^2 \\
&\qquad= \boxed{2x^9 - 8x^7 + 9x^6 - 16x^5 - 12x^4 + 9x^3 - 24x^2}.
\end{align*}

First, we use the distributive property to expand the first two factors:

\begin{align*}
6(x+2)(x+3) &= (6\cdot x + 6 \cdot 2) (x+3)\\
&=(6x+12)(x+3)
\end{align*}We use the distributive property again by adding the product of $ 6x+12 $ and $ x $ to the product of $ 6x+12 $ and 3:

\begin{align*}
(6x+12)(x+3) &= (6x+12) \cdot x +(6x+12) \cdot 3\\
&= x(6x+12) + 3(6x+12)
\end{align*}We use the distributive property again and combine like terms:

\begin{align*}
x(6x+12) + 3(6x+12) &= 6x^2 + 12x + 18x+ 36\\
&= \boxed{6x^2 + 30x + 36}
\end{align*}

Combining like terms, we find that  \begin{align*}
(9x^2+3x+7)+&(3x^2+7x^5+2)\\
&=(9x^2+3x^2)+(7+2)+7x^5+3x\\
&=\boxed{7x^5+12x^2+3x+9}.
\end{align*}

Combining like terms, we find that  \begin{align*}
&(x^5+3x^2+3x^5)-(x^7+2x^2+6x^5)\\
&\qquad=(x^5+3x^5-6x^5)+(3x^2-2x^2)-x^7\\
&\qquad=\boxed{-x^7-2x^5+x^2}.
\end{align*}

Instead of expanding the entire product, we can look only at terms that will multiply to give $ x^3 $.  We know that $$x^3=x^3\cdot 1=x^2\cdot x=x\cdot x^2=1\cdot x^3.$$Knowing this, the $ x^3 $ term in the expansion will be the sum of these four terms: $$(6x^3)(4)+(4x^2)(3x)+(-7x)(3x^2)+(-5)(6x^3).$$We simplify to find: \begin{align*}
&(6x^3)(4)+(4x^2)(3x)+(-7x)(3x^2)+(-5)(6x^3)\\
&\qquad=24x^3+12x^3-21x^3-30x^3\\
&\qquad=\boxed{-15}x^3
\end{align*}

When using the distributive property for the first time, we add the product of $ 2p^2 - 1 $ and $ 3p^2 $ to the product of $ 2p^2 - 1 $ and $ 4 $:

\begin{align*}
(2p^2 - 1)(3p^2 + 4) &= (2p^2 - 1) \cdot (3p^2) + (2p^2 - 1) \cdot 4
\end{align*}We use the distributive property again and combine like terms:

\begin{align*}
(3p^2)(2p^2 - 1) + 4(2p^2 - 1) &= 6p^4 - 3p^2 + 8p^2 - 4\\
&= \boxed{6p^4 + 5p^2 - 4}
\end{align*}

