&\quad + \frac{c^5}{(c - a)(c - b)(c - d)(c - e)} + \frac{d^5}{(d - a)(d - b)(d - c)(d - e)} \\
&\quad + \frac{e^5}{(e - a)(e - b)(e - c)(e - d)}.
\end{align*}

fields.solution:
Since three of the roots of $ p(x) $ are 1, 2, and 3, we can write
\[p(x) = (x - 1)(x - 2)(x - 3)(x - r).\]Then
\begin{align*}
p(0) + p(4) &= (-1)(-2)(-3)(-r) + (3)(2)(1)(4 - r) \\
&= 6r + 24 - 6r = \boxed{24}.
\end{align*}

